quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  33,59,"O Prophet! Ask your wives, daughters, and believing women to draw their cloaks over their bodies. In this way it is more likely that they will be recognized ˹as virtuous˺ and not be harassed. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and rumour-mongers in Medina do not desist, We will certainly incite you ˹O Prophet˺ against them, and then they will not be your neighbours there any longer"
  33,61,"˹They deserve to be˺ condemned. ˹If they were to persist,˺ they would get themselves seized and killed relentlessly wherever they are found"
  33,62,That was Allah’s way with those ˹hypocrites˺ who have gone before. And you will find no change in Allah’s way
  33,63,"People ask you ˹O Prophet˺ about the Hour. Say, “That knowledge is only with Allah. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.”"
  33,64,"Surely Allah condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and ever—never will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ˹constantly˺ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, “Oh! If only we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger!”"
  33,67,"And they will say, “Our Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ˹Right˺ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ˹our˺ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.”"